---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Terms of Service | Schedule.Makeup',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 mx-auto lg:px-8 lg:py-20 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="font-bold font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tighter tracking-tighter mb-8">Terms of Service</h1>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-4xl dark:prose-invert">
      <p>Welcome to Schedule.Makeup. By using our services, you agree to the following terms regarding your professional vanity URL and booking setup.</p>
      
      <h3>1. Service Description</h3>
      <p>Schedule.Makeup provides a one-time "White-Glove" setup for makeup artists and studio owners. This includes a custom vanity URL (yourname.schedule.makeup) and a mobile-optimized booking interface.</p>

      <h3>2. One-Time Payment & Lifetime Access</h3>
      <p>The $99 fee is a one-time setup and licensing fee. There are no monthly recurring SaaS fees for the core vanity URL redirection and hosting of the landing page provided at setup.</p>

      <h3>3. Ownership of Vanity URL</h3>
      <p>Your vanity URL is assigned to you for the life of the Schedule.Makeup platform. We reserve the right to reclaim URLs that are inactive for more than 24 months or used for prohibited content.</p>

      <h3>4. Setup Timeline</h3>
      <p>We aim for "Same-Day Setup" for orders placed before 2 PM EST on business days. Accuracy of information provided (services, availability) is the responsibility of the Studio Owner.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
